items.content:
Welcome to our study!

Please read the following information before you decide to participate. Your participation is voluntary. When you finish, click the "Accept and Continue" button at the bottom of this page to proceed.

Study Information

1. Purpose:

In this study, we investigate how the human brain infers rules and applies them. By participating, you will get an insight into our research, and you will further help us to gain new insights into human cognition.

2. Confidentiality:

We save the data under a randomly assigned participant number and thus totally anonymized on a server of Tübingen University. All people that have access to your personal data are obliged to maintain data secrecy. If data from this study is published, this will happen in an anonymized manner. Hence, your data cannot be assigned to you.

3. Voluntary participation and right to withdraw:

Your participation in this research is entirely voluntary, you can withdraw at any time. There will be no negative repercussions. You do not need to provide a reason for your withdrawal. If you withdraw from the study before data collection is completed, your data will not be used.

4. Risks:

Your participation does not involve any physical or emotional risk to you. You are free to withdraw at any time.

5. Data storage and sharing:

We will share this data with other researchers. If the study does not result in a scientific publication, we will store the data on a password-protected university server for a maximum of 5 years. Since the data is stored completely anonymized, we cannot delete your data once it has been saved.

items.title: Introduction
items.content: In this study, you will view pairs of matrices: an input and its corresponding output after a rule has been applied (see example below).
After observing two examples (illustrating the same rule), you will decide whether that rule applies to a new pair.
Press y for “yes” and n for “no.”

items.title: Test Trial
items.content: Next, you will complete a short practice trial to get familiar with the task.
This trial is only for practice — your responses will not be recorded.

17.content:
Feedback Questionnaire

This short survey asks about your experience with the task. Please answer honestly.

1. How difficult did you find the task?
2. How confident were you in your decisions during probe trials?
3. Did you use a specific strategy to infer the rules?
4. Were you able to stay attentive and engaged throughout?
